### Swift ###
# Xcode
#
# gitignore contributors: remember to update the values below if you switch to a new IDE / Editor. Thanks for your understanding!
# https://www.toptal.com/developers/gitignore/api/swift

## User settings
xcuserdata/
*.pbxuser
*.mode1v3
*.mode2v3
*.perspectivev3
*.xcworkspace/xcuserdata/

## compatibility with Xcode 8 and later XCSupport files
*.xccompat.idsvc
*.xcworkspace/xcshareddata/IDEWorkspaceChecks.plist

## compatibility with Xcode 3 and earlier (ignoring all vendor code)
build/
DerivedData/
*.moved-aside
*.pbxuser
*.mode1v3
*.mode2v3
*.perspectivev3
*.xcworkspace
!*.xcworkspace/contents.xcworkspacedata
profile
*.hmap
*.ipa
*.xcarchive
*.dSYM.zip
*.dSYM

## Playgrounds
timeline.xctimeline

## Swift Package Manager
#
# Add this line if you want to avoid checking in source code from Swift Package Manager dependencies.
# Packages/
# Package.resolved
# *.xcodeproj
#
# Xcode automatically generates this directory with a .gitkeep file (so your project doesn't have to) but be aware that not checking it in is sometimes a mistake.
# !Pods/

## CocoaPods
#
# We recommend against adding the Pods directory to your .gitignore. However
# if you do want to ignore the pods directory, uncomment the following lines:
Pods/
Podfile.lock
.pods/

## Carthage
#
# Add this line if you want to avoid checking in source code from Carthage dependencies.
Carthage/Checkouts
Carthage/Build/

## Accio dependency management
Dependencies/
.accio/

## fastlane
#
# It is recommended to not store the screenshots in the git repo.
# However, in case you do want to add screenshots, ensure they are not of
# your screenshots that may contain sensitive data like emails as seen in
# https://snyk.io/blog/remove-sensitive-data-from-git-history-by-using-git-filter-branch/
#
# Note: fastlane/screenshots and fastlane/preview.html are deprecated, use fastlane/screenshots.html instead instead.
fastlane/screenshots
fastlane/preview.html

## Code Injection
#
# After new code Injection tools there's a generated folder /iOSInjectionProject
# https://github.com/johnno1962/injectionforxcode

iOSInjectionProject/

